pr_title: GSoC Project Cross Slide Coordinated Viewing First Milestone
pr_body:
<!--- Provide a short summary of your changes in the Title -->

## Summary
<!--- Describe the changes in more detail. Feel free to include screenshots if relevant. -->
In this milestone I have implemented the options for choosing which slide to view in the viewer page and have implemented pagination, sorting and filtering as was discussed with @nanli-emory. In the cross viewer I have implemented independent panning, zooming, adding labels, adding rulers, adding annotations , viewing layer managers for both the slides. using magnifier tool and the screenshot feature which takes screenshot of both the slides and joins them together. 

## Motivation
<!--- Why have you made this Pull Request? Does this fix an open issue? -->
This is the first Milestone of my GSoC Project Cross Slide Coordinated Viewing.

## Testing
<!--- Has this been tested beyond the automatic hooks? How so? -->
I have tested this feature in Google Chrome and Firefox and everything seems to be working fine.

## Questions
<!--- Are there any aspects you're unsure about? Are you looking for any feedback? -->

<!--- Mark a pull request as a draft to signal that it is not ready for review. -->

pr_title: Third Milestone : Cross Slide Coordinated Viewing
pr_body:
<!--- Provide a short summary of your changes in the Title -->

## Summary
<!--- Describe the changes in more detail. Feel free to include screenshots if relevant. -->
* Added rotation support for viewing heatmaps and annotations.
* Added rotation support to slide sync.
* Added rotation support in Slide Capture
* Added tutorial in cross slide viewer.

## Motivation
<!--- Why have you made this Pull Request? Does this fix an open issue? -->

## Testing
<!--- Has this been tested beyond the automatic hooks? How so? -->
Tested the features in my local development environment
**Browser** : Google Chrome
**OS** : Linux
## Questions
<!--- Are there any aspects you're unsure about? Are you looking for any feedback? -->

<!--- Mark a pull request as a draft to signal that it is not ready for review. -->
## Screenshots
* Slide Capture on rotated slides with heatmaps and annotations
![sampleCapture](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48997514/127758835-e231f06b-d0e7-483d-abdc-0d15e305ab92.jpeg)

* View recording of the features [here](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1HOp25TqShKJHoUminQwtQP6A_vfmbbfW/view?usp=sharing)
